A common "Logic Smell" here is the "Integer Division" bug, 
where 'count / capacity' in Java truncates the decimal 
before Math.ceil() can process it. Ensuring the cast to 
(double), or using '(count + capacity - 1) / capacity', 
eliminated this hidden bug right from the start.

